WEBVTT

00:02.338 --> 00:08.864
Helen, I'm Dr. Jonathan Barker, pastor here at Amazing Grace Baptist Church in Mount area, North Carolina.

00:09.545 --> 00:14.890
I would like to personally thank you for taking out time today to tune in to our preaching podcast.

00:15.431 --> 00:18.954
We hope that this message will be a great encouragement to your heart today.

00:19.475 --> 00:20.936
Galatians chapter number six.

00:24.640 --> 00:31.186
I first, I first had this, this thought a couple months back when brother Josh,

00:31.586 --> 00:34.450
preached on, throw another log on the fire.

00:35.131 --> 00:40.457
And I've never had, never just never got liberty to preach it until, until today.

00:48.407 --> 00:55.436
But if you found your place, you'd stand in Galatians chapter number six, and we're going to start in verse number seven.

00:57.539 --> 00:59.922
Be not deceived, God is not mocked.

01:00.226 --> 01:14.225
for whatsoever remains soth, he shall also reap, for he that soth to the flesh of the flesh shall reap corruption, but he that soth to the spirit shall of the spirit reap ever life everlasting."

01:14.245 --> 01:22.657
Paul starts this with a warning, be not deceived, because the greatest deception is not what others say, it's what we tell ourselves.

01:23.438 --> 01:29.266
We convince ourselves that the small choices don't matter, that the compromises won't hurt anyone,

01:29.698 --> 01:32.282
that we can feed the flesh and still walk in the spirit.

01:32.302 --> 01:33.744
But God says it doesn't work that way.

01:34.305 --> 01:35.547
Once you reap, you will sow.

01:35.687 --> 01:36.809
Once you sow, you will reap.

01:38.051 --> 01:52.693
Isaiah 9, 18 says, for wickedness, burneth as fire, it shall devour briars and thorns and shall kinder and kindle in the thickets of the forest and shall mount up like the lifting of the smoke.

01:52.713 --> 01:56.018
Isaiah sees the wickedness of Israel as a raging wildfire.

01:56.130 --> 01:58.974
Swift and uncontrollable and devouring everything it touches.

01:59.434 --> 02:02.939
Inside every one of us there are two fires competing for fuel.

02:03.159 --> 02:06.023
One is the fire of the flesh and the other is the fire of the spirit.

02:06.304 --> 02:11.370
And every day our choices and every day by our choices we decide which one gets fed.

02:12.231 --> 02:13.754
Every person is feeding something.

02:14.595 --> 02:17.098
Fire, it don't grow all at once.

02:17.118 --> 02:18.940
It grows by what you keep adding to it.

02:19.201 --> 02:26.130
A small spark fed consistently becomes a flame and a flame fed long enough becomes a fire you can't ignore.

02:26.978 --> 02:28.380
That's exactly what Paul's talking about here.

02:28.600 --> 02:32.885
What you sow you reap, what you feed grows and what you starve will eventually die.

02:34.127 --> 02:42.817
Every thought you entertain, every habit you allow, every time you disobey the Holy Spirit, you're either adding fire to the fuel of the Spirit, you're feeding the fire of the flesh.

02:43.518 --> 02:45.160
The question is, which fire are you feeding?

02:47.042 --> 02:48.985
First is the fire of the Spirit.

02:50.046 --> 02:56.594
2 Timothy 1, 6 says, wherefore I put the in remembrance that thou stir stir up

02:56.866 --> 03:00.630
the gift of God, which is in thee by putting on of my hands.

03:01.531 --> 03:03.053
The words stir up.

03:03.954 --> 03:04.975
That's what I want to focus on here.

03:05.356 --> 03:14.646
Anyone, anyone who's set by fire knows when you take a stick and you start, you start when it starts to down down and you start stirring up them coals, them embers.

03:14.686 --> 03:16.928
The hidden embers and they start to change.

03:17.229 --> 03:18.390
They rise to the surface.

03:18.430 --> 03:20.993
The flame that looks like it was dying starts coming back to life.

03:21.233 --> 03:22.174
The heat increases.

03:22.234 --> 03:23.236
Nothing news added.

03:23.556 --> 03:25.458
What was already there is just activated.

03:25.634 --> 03:30.480
That's what Paul's telling Timothy, if you're saved, you're on fire for God's, the fire for God's already in you.

03:30.520 --> 03:33.564
It hasn't disappeared and it can't be taken away and it never will disappear.

03:34.185 --> 03:35.767
It just, you just need to be stirred up.

03:36.068 --> 03:38.111
A fire let alone will always die down.

03:40.594 --> 03:47.623
If we stir, if we stir the fire of the spirit to, if we want to stir the fire of the spirit, we have to obey the Holy Spirit.

03:48.985 --> 03:52.850
Even if it's uncomfortable, when I first started preaching, it was,

03:53.890 --> 03:56.233
It still is nerve-wracking.

03:56.253 --> 03:57.795
I didn't eat lunch today because I felt sick.

04:02.021 --> 04:04.304
We have to raise our hand.

04:04.324 --> 04:05.325
We have to shout amen.

04:05.506 --> 04:06.447
Go to the altar.

04:06.587 --> 04:08.209
Stop letting the flesh get in the way.

04:08.830 --> 04:10.352
We have to worship when we don't feel it.

04:10.372 --> 04:14.157
We have to open his word and read his word when we don't want to.

04:17.762 --> 04:20.306
We have to worship him when our flesh wants distraction.

04:21.027 --> 04:22.469
Stirring requires movement.

04:22.489 --> 04:23.570
It requires an effort.

04:23.682 --> 04:24.904
It requires intention.

04:24.964 --> 04:26.006
It has to be intentional.

04:29.131 --> 04:31.535
When fire is stirred, conviction comes back.

04:31.935 --> 04:35.721
The things that you were comfortable with start bothering you again.

04:35.802 --> 04:37.624
Sin you ignored, starts come to the surface.

04:38.205 --> 04:41.791
When a fire is stirred, prayer isn't forced.

04:41.811 --> 04:43.414
Worship isn't silent.

04:43.674 --> 04:45.637
The Word of God ain't just words on a page.

04:46.439 --> 04:48.562
A stirred fire burns hotter.

04:48.770 --> 04:51.313
When a fire's stirred, power returns.

04:51.373 --> 04:52.574
Power to stay noticed in.

04:52.614 --> 04:53.976
Power to stand when others bow.

04:54.316 --> 04:57.560
Power to speak when fear says to stay quiet.

05:00.043 --> 05:07.291
A stirred fire, the flames become brighter and the people around you can see something that's different about you.

05:07.311 --> 05:11.736
Paul ain't telling Timothy to ask God for more fire.

05:11.776 --> 05:15.400
He's telling them not to neglect the fire that he already had.

05:15.961 --> 05:17.042
So I ask you church,

05:17.282 --> 05:20.245
Has your fire been stirred lately or are you letting the embers die down?

05:23.469 --> 05:25.831
Second, the fire of the flesh.

05:27.893 --> 05:37.444
Romans 13, 14 says, but put ye on the Lord Jesus Christ and make not provision for the flesh to fulfill the lust thereof.

05:38.425 --> 05:42.509
Every fire needs fuel and so does the flesh.

05:42.589 --> 05:45.853
Paul doesn't say that the flesh is going to disappear when we get saved.

05:45.873 --> 05:46.994
It's always going to be there.

05:47.522 --> 05:49.785
He says, don't make provisions for it.

05:50.005 --> 05:51.287
The flesh is still present.

05:51.727 --> 05:54.050
It's still hungry and it's still dangerous if it's fed.

05:54.691 --> 06:01.140
The fire of the flesh is fed when we allow our hearts by what we allow in our hearts and our minds.

06:02.301 --> 06:05.145
What we allow to live in our mind eventually controls our actions.

06:05.725 --> 06:10.291
A thought entertained becomes a desire, a desire of fed becomes a decision.

06:11.092 --> 06:11.853
Think about David.

06:11.893 --> 06:15.538
When he saw Bathsheba set bathing on her roof,

06:16.354 --> 06:18.536
Just sin wasn't a sin, but he looked too long.

06:20.358 --> 06:22.100
He let that thought take a hold of his mind.

06:22.561 --> 06:30.049
He allowed that thought to grow into a desire and he continues to dwell on her, eventually committing adultery and murder to cover up his sin.

06:31.370 --> 06:34.834
I don't think David woke up that morning planning on doing all that.

06:35.795 --> 06:39.539
He just, he woke up idle and he looked too long.

06:39.879 --> 06:46.226
He entertained the thought and what the mind entertained the flesh demanded.

06:47.170 --> 06:50.093
what we watch, what we listen to, what we dwell on.

06:51.094 --> 06:52.855
It's not neutral, it's fuel.

06:53.776 --> 06:56.859
But the question is, what fire does it fuel?

06:58.381 --> 07:00.022
The flesh always wants more.

07:00.062 --> 07:01.704
You can never satisfy it.

07:02.245 --> 07:05.067
The more you feed it, the harder it is for you to put down.

07:05.888 --> 07:16.178
The fire of the flesh feeds on compromise, this obedience, pride, unforgiveness, that secret sin that you think nobody knows about, but God knows.

07:17.154 --> 07:19.957
Just like any fire, the more it's fed, the stronger it becomes.

07:21.419 --> 07:23.962
Think about a growing when you starve fire and it's growing.

07:24.423 --> 07:27.186
You can hear the sounds, the crackles, the pop, the roar.

07:27.727 --> 07:29.289
You can hear a forest fire for miles.

07:30.350 --> 07:32.433
But if you're right next to it, it's all you can hear.

07:34.375 --> 07:38.420
You better be careful feeling the wrong fire because sin can get so loud.

07:39.021 --> 07:43.166
It can become so loud that it becomes hard to heal the steel, small voice of the Holy Spirit.

07:44.948 --> 07:46.610
When we fail to hear his voice,

07:46.754 --> 07:51.301
When we fail to hear his voice warning us to turn back, that's how we drift.

07:51.661 --> 07:58.812
It's not all at once, but it's slowly by feeding the fire of the flesh instead of fueling the fire of the spirit.

07:58.832 --> 08:03.339
What's bothered us no longer does, what's what convicts us now feels normal.

08:04.000 --> 08:09.588
Convention doesn't disappear, it just gets drowned out by the deafening roar of the fire of the flesh.

08:10.129 --> 08:11.531
And that's a dangerous place to be.

08:13.454 --> 08:16.178
When we feed the flesh, we are intentionally trying to put

08:16.354 --> 08:17.956
the spirits fire out all at once.

08:18.236 --> 08:19.857
We just throw a little bit of water on it.

08:19.877 --> 08:22.740
Just continually, the more we do it, just a little bit more water each time.

08:23.541 --> 08:27.485
One compromise, one act of disobedience, one ignored conviction.

08:27.865 --> 08:29.887
A little water doesn't kill a fire immediately.

08:30.148 --> 08:31.289
It just lowers the flame.

08:31.929 --> 08:34.993
Each time we feed the flesh, we cool the fire of the spirit.

08:35.433 --> 08:38.576
Each time we ignore God's voice, that flame gets smaller and smaller.

08:39.417 --> 08:42.260
Each time conviction is resisted, the heat fades.

08:42.740 --> 08:44.562
And if we keep doing that over and over,

08:46.338 --> 08:48.260
We don't end up with a blazing fire anymore.

08:48.641 --> 08:50.022
We end up with a small ember.

08:50.623 --> 08:51.764
An ember still exists.

08:51.844 --> 08:56.770
It will never, it will always exist, but it no longer gives off much heat and no longer gives off light.

08:58.371 --> 08:59.973
An ember that no one else can see.

09:00.754 --> 09:04.538
And that's the danger because the embers, because those embers don't draw people in.

09:04.919 --> 09:06.080
They don't warm anyone.

09:06.380 --> 09:07.502
They don't light the way.

09:07.802 --> 09:09.384
The Bible doesn't say manage the flesh.

09:09.404 --> 09:10.745
It says, make no provision for it.

09:10.906 --> 09:12.107
You can't tame this fire.

09:12.167 --> 09:13.488
Don't compromise with this fire.

09:13.508 --> 09:14.930
You have to starve the fire.

09:19.266 --> 09:22.932
Number three, you can't feed both fires.

09:25.155 --> 09:33.248
Matthew 624 says, no man can serve two masters for he or either hate, hate the one and love the other or else he will hold to one and despise the other.

09:33.548 --> 09:36.112
You cannot serve God and the mammon and mammon.

09:36.733 --> 09:37.995
It's real, it's simple.

09:38.976 --> 09:42.903
Every habit, every choice, every thought you entertain is feeding one fire or the other.

09:43.824 --> 09:46.027
Neutral, being neutral is a lie from the enemy.

09:46.368 --> 09:47.730
You can't build a fire

09:48.066 --> 09:49.388
while throwing water on it.

09:49.809 --> 09:50.890
There's no middle ground.

09:51.311 --> 09:57.540
We're either sowing the flesh or we are sowing to the flesh or sowing to the spirit.

09:57.560 --> 09:58.862
Which fire are you feeding?

10:01.406 --> 10:05.673
We don't get to choose when we'll stand before God.

10:05.693 --> 10:08.157
Every one of us is born feeding the fire of the flesh.

10:09.218 --> 10:13.805
And the Bible tells us that in the end, the end of that fire of the flesh is death and hell.

10:15.007 --> 10:15.948
But God is mercy.

10:15.968 --> 10:17.010
He did not leave us there.

10:17.602 --> 10:19.424
Jesus stepped into that fire force.

10:20.085 --> 10:21.887
He took our judgment, we deserved.

10:21.907 --> 10:22.648
He bore the wrath.

10:22.668 --> 10:26.312
He paid the price so that we could receive eternal life.

10:27.593 --> 10:32.578
Galatians 6 says, he that sowed to the spirit shall reap the spirit.

10:34.120 --> 10:39.166
He that sowed to the spirit shall all the spirit reap life everlasting.

10:39.186 --> 10:42.790
That life ain't, it ain't earned by good works.

10:42.810 --> 10:44.231
It's not earned by trying harder.

10:44.552 --> 10:46.674
It's received from repentance and faith.

10:47.426 --> 10:49.068
God doesn't ask you to manage your sin.

10:49.088 --> 10:50.611
He asks you to surrender it to Him.

10:51.292 --> 10:52.433
He asks you to come to Him.

10:54.536 --> 10:55.898
Jesus paid that price for you.

10:57.681 --> 11:03.289
If you don't have the fire, the Spirit in you today, today's the day to change that.

11:04.050 --> 11:07.135
Come to the altar and ask God into your heart.

11:07.155 --> 11:09.017
That fire will be the best thing you ever do.

11:10.640 --> 11:15.026
Maybe you're here today and you're saved and you have that fire, but you've been feeding the wrong one.

11:15.650 --> 11:17.321
Don't wait, don't reason it away.

11:18.408 --> 11:20.301
Don't throw water on the fire anymore.

11:20.925 --> 11:22.354
Today's the day to get things right.

